      {
        "id": "af50cead3bfdddd9e2af1f0463a7f26b930823a9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3239,
          "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramverma"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-29 11:09:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1\n\nIn Apex, the way of making REST requests to other system is by using RESTREQUESTOR.\nHow it works is, your task logic needs to produce an output event which makes the body of the REST request.\nThe URL, method and other parameters are configured in the config file of apex.\nAnd the response is treated as event to trigger another policy in apex.\nHave a look at the examples-onap-vcpe sub-module in apex-pdp.\nThis use case also makes a call to Guard, A&AI & APPC.\n\nI am OK to approve this now, but we should open a JIRA to fix this in next release.",
        "patchset_number": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "753c42c26bbbb49cfbb2eb7742e82ba3068072a6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-29 11:15:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nMy understanding is the BBS use case for Policy is a POC. I would like Liam to review first before merge.",
        "patchset_number": 7
